<MainLayout
  title="Eden Grazing Services | Land Management | Soul Miner's Eden"
  description="Sustainable land management through rotational grazing. Natural vegetation control for retention ponds, solar farms, HOAs, and commercial properties in Athens, Georgia."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-accent-600 to-accent-700 text-white py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-accent-200 font-medium mb-4 uppercase tracking-wide">Eden Grazing Services</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-display font-bold mb-6">
          Goats. Doing What Goats Do.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-accent-100 mb-8">
          We bring goats to your property. They eat the stuff you don't want. You save money. Pretty straightforward, honestly.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a href="/land-management/how-it-works" class="btn bg-white text-accent-700 hover:bg-accent-50 text-lg px-8 py-4">
            See How It Works
          </a>
          <a href="/land-management/request" class="btn border-2 border-white text-white hover:bg-white/10 text-lg px-8 py-4">
            Request Assessment
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container-custom py-16">
    <!-- Problem / Solution Section -->
    <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-warm-900 mb-8">
        Look, Here's the Thing
      </h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-warm-700 space-y-6">
        <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed">
          Mowing gets expensive. Fast. Especially if you've got a big property out near Watkinsville or down by Winterville. Then there's the chemicals. The fuel costs. The guy who didn't show up last Tuesday.
        </p>

        <p>
          Here's the thing though. Goats have been doing this job forever. Way before John Deere came along. They actually like eating kudzu and privet and all that stuff you're fighting. It's not work to them. It's lunch.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-accent-50 border-l-4 border-accent-500 p-6 rounded-r-lg my-8">
          <p class="text-warm-800 font-medium italic">
            "The level of production needed to sustain our growing population will not be possible without land capable of carrying that load. Agriculturalists of all kinds have no choice but to improve. It's in their best interest too."
          </p>
          <p class="text-accent-700 font-semibold mt-4">
            Land's got to last. Can't just keep dumping chemicals on it and hope for the best.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p>
          So yeah. We bring goats. They eat. Bo checks on them. We move them around. Your property looks better. That's basically it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Target Properties -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-warm-900 mb-4 text-center">
        Where Goats Work Best
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-warm-600 text-center mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        We serve properties around Athens and Northeast Georgia. If you've got vegetation that needs managing, we can probably help.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        {targetProperties.map((property) => (
          <div class="feature-box flex gap-6">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-accent-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
              {property.icon === "water" && (
                <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-accent-700" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19.428 15.428a2 2 0 00-1.022-.547l-2.387-.477a6 6 0 00-3.86.517l-.318.158a6 6 0 01-3.86.517L6.05 15.21a2 2 0 00-1.806.547M8 4h8l-1 1v5.172a2 2 0 00.586 1.414l5 5c1.26 1.26.367 3.414-1.415 3.414H4.828c-1.782 0-2.674-2.154-1.414-3.414l5-5A2 2 0 009 10.172V5L8 4z" />
                </svg>
              )}
              {property.icon === "sun" && (
                <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-accent-700" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 3v1m0 16v1m9-9h-1M4 12H3m15.364 6.364l-.707-.707M6.343 6.343l-.707-.707m12.728 0l-.707.707M6.343 17.657l-.707.707M16 12a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0z" />
                </svg>
              )}
              {property.icon === "home" && (
                <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-accent-700" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 12l2-2m0 0l7-7 7 7M5 10v10a1 1 0 001 1h3m10-11l2 2m-2-2v10a1 1 0 01-1 1h-3m-6 0a1 1 0 001-1v-4a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v4a1 1 0 001 1m-6 0h6" />
                </svg>
              )}
              {property.icon === "building" && (
                <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-accent-700" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v16m14 0h2m-2 0h-5m-9 0H3m2 0h5M9 7h1m-1 4h1m4-4h1m-1 4h1m-5 10v-5a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v5m-4 0h4" />
                </svg>
              )}
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-warm-900">{property.name}</h3>
              <p class="text-warm-600">{property.description}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Benefits Grid -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-warm-900 mb-4 text-center">
        Why Goats?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-warm-600 text-center mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        We help folks find natural solutions for natural problems. That's kind of our thing.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {benefits.map((benefit) => (
          <div class="bg-white border border-secondary-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-accent-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
